+---
+target: REGULATION.md
+meeting: context_harness/operator/meetings/2026-04-23_swift_impl_delegation_and_vibe_limits.md
+supersedes:
+  - REGULATION.md#section-2-the-two-operators
+  - REGULATION.md#section-5-1-gate-5-process-integrity
+  - REGULATION.md#section-7-operator-layer-drift-audit
+  - REGULATION.md#new-section-12-multi-axis-evaluation
+  - REGULATION.md#new-section-13-vibe-coding-regulation
+---
+
+# REGULATION Amendment — Swift Implementation Delegation And Vibe-Coding Controls
+
+## Purpose
+
+User directive on 2026-04-23 narrows operator responsibilities:
+
+- Claude Code Operator must not directly edit Swift implementation files.
+- Swift implementation must be performed by Codex subagent/fork dispatch.
+- Claude Code Operator authors meetings, contracts, briefs, evidence, and orchestration.
+- Codex authors Swift code and participates in review/verdict.
+
+This amendment also adds multi-axis evaluation and explicit vibe-coding regulation based on `docs/design-docs/vibe-coding-limits-2026.md`.
+
+## Proposed Change — REG §2 The Two Operators
+
+Add:
+
+```markdown
+### Swift implementation delegation
+
+Claude Code Operator does not directly edit `workspace/ios/**/*.swift`, `workspace/ios/project.yml`, or Swift test files during implementation stages.
+
+Swift implementation is delegated to a Codex subagent/fork dispatch operating under the active round contract and whitelist. The dispatch must receive:
+
+- active round id and lock path,
+- exact file whitelist,
+- spec/acceptance/eval protocol paths,
+- reusable-asset requirements,
+- forbidden patterns,
+- evidence expectations.
+
+Claude Code Operator may author or edit:
+
+- meetings,
+- contracts,
+- implementation briefs,
+- evidence capture,
+- process logs,
+- non-Swift docs within whitelist.
+
+Codex may author Swift implementation files within the active whitelist. Claude Code captures factual evidence. Codex writes the verdict.
+```
+
+## Proposed Change — REG §5.1 Gate 5 Process Integrity
+
+Add blocker:
+
+```markdown
+- Operator modified Swift implementation files directly instead of dispatching to Codex subagent/fork.
+```
+
+Clarification:
+
+```markdown
+For this blocker, "operator modified directly" means a Swift file changed without a matching Codex implementation transcript, dispatch brief, or process-log event tying the change to a Codex implementation worker for the active round.
+```
+
+## Proposed Change — REG §7 Operator-Layer Drift Audit
+
+Add enforced or manual-audit check:
+
+```markdown
+No direct operator edit to `workspace/ios/**/*.swift`.
+
+Until automated, Gate 5 evidence must include:
+
+- `git log --name-status <base_commit>..HEAD -- workspace/ios`
+- Codex dispatch transcript path(s) and SHA-256
+- changed Swift file list
+- mapping from changed Swift file to Codex dispatch id
+
+If any changed Swift file lacks a Codex dispatch mapping, Gate 5 blocks.
+```
+
+Future checker implementation:
+
+```markdown
+The checker should validate the changed Swift file list against process-log events with `actor=codex` and a recorded transcript/hash. A git blame scan may be used as supporting evidence but is not sufficient by itself because author identity can be configured locally.
+```
+
+## Proposed New REG §12 Multi-Axis Evaluation
+
+Add:
+
+```markdown
+## §12. Multi-Axis Evaluation
+
+Gate 2 for implementation rounds must include all five axes:
+
+1. **Code correctness** — unit tests, compile/build, state transition tests, and touched-file review.
+2. **Real runtime function** — simulator launch or runtime capture showing the changed flow works in app context.
+3. **UI/UX fidelity** — screenshot comparison against active design contracts, Deepsight mocks, or accepted placeholders.
+4. **Navigation and information consistency** — labels, routes, state restoration, data shown, and user-facing copy match product contract.
+5. **Process-context soundness** — evidence that the implementation followed the active contract, whitelist, delegation rule, lint rules, and documented unresolved assumptions.
+
+Any axis not applicable must be explicitly marked `not applicable` with reason in the evidence report. Silent omission is a Gate 5 blocker.
+```
+
+## Proposed New REG §13 Vibe-Coding Regulation
+
+Add:
+
+```markdown
+## §13. Vibe-Coding Regulation
+
+Every Swift implementation dispatch must consult:
+
+`docs/design-docs/vibe-coding-limits-2026.md`
+
+The dispatch brief must include a "Vibe-coding risk controls" section covering:
+
+- reusable asset plan,
+- architecture coherence,
+- memory/concurrency/error handling,
+- UI/UX runtime evidence,
+- accessibility,
+- security/dependency risk,
+- testing depth,
+- data-model mapping,
+- unchecked assumptions.
+
+Codex implementation output is treated as untrusted until:
+
+1. build/test evidence passes,
+2. forbidden-pattern grep passes,
+3. runtime evidence exists for user-facing changes,
+4. cross-operator review records at least one concrete challenge/risk or factual no-issue evidence,
+5. verdict cites evidence for every acceptance criterion.
+```
+
+## Migration Notes
+
+- This amendment does not invalidate prior rounds retroactively.
+- It applies to future Swift implementation rounds after adoption.
+- Existing Swift files may be edited by Codex dispatch under whitelist; Claude Code may inspect/read them for evidence and review prompts but not modify them directly.
